ws-2/the-pixabay-license-7823/\">in 2019</a>. Prior to that change, Pixabay used the <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20190108204845/https://pixabay.com/en/service/terms/\">CC0 waiver</a>. Therefore, old images are <a href=\"https://pixabay.com/it/forum/official-pixabay-news-2/the-pixabay-license-7823/?pagi=4\">still in the public domain</a>, despite being <a href=\"https://pixabay.com/it/forum/official-pixabay-news-2/the-pixabay-license-7823/?pagi=4\">misleadingly tagged</a> with the Pixabay License. Before using an image, check what the state of the <a href=\"https://pixabay.com/service/\">terms of service</a> was at that point in time.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T17:11:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"johnjago/awesome-uncopyright","categoryHTML":"<h2>Images</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pxhere.com/it/license\">PxHere</a> - To find and upload CC0 images.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T17:11:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"johnjago/awesome-uncopyright","categoryHTML":"<h2>Images</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.rijksmuseum.nl/en/rijksstudio\">Rijksstudio</a> - Rijksmuseum digitised and made available public domain works from several artists including Rembrandt, Vermeer, and others.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T17:11:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"johnjago/awesome-uncopyright","categoryHTML":"<h2>Images</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://skitterphoto.com/license\">Skitterphoto</a> - A place to upload and find CC0 images.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T17:11:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"johnjago/awesome-uncopyright","categoryHTML":"<h2>Images</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.spacex.com/media\">SpaceX media</a> - SpaceX media <strong>no longer</strong> lists its images as being in the public domain. Even on <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20170412063800/https://www.flickr.com/photos/spacex/16787988882/\">Flickr</a>, it uses a CC-BY-NC license. However, old images (from <a href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20150328140645/http://www.spacex.com/media\">here</a> to <a href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20191122175115/https://www.spacex.com/media\">here</a>) had indeed been placed into the public domain and have no copyright restriction (including some images on <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20170412063800/https://www.flickr.com/photos/spacex/16787988882/\">Flickr</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T17:11:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"johnjago/awesome-uncopyright","categoryHTML":"<h2>Images</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Old images on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/\">Unsplash</a>. Unsplash <strong>no longer</strong> uses CC0, so new images are not in the public domain (but all images released before the license change still are).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T17:11:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hbokh/awesome-saltstack","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogposts and opinions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@Joachim8675309/vagrant-provisioning-with-saltstack-50dab12ce6c7\">Vagrant Provisioning with SaltStack</a> - Provisioning Virtual System using Masterless Salt Stack.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T16:37:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hbokh/awesome-saltstack","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogposts and opinions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@Joachim8675309/salt-devkit-with-external-formulas-9e38d8b90cd7\">Salt DevKit with External Formulas</a> - Local Development with Vagrant using external Salt formulas.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T16:37:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aliesbelik/awesome-jmeter","categoryHTML":"<h2>Official Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jmeter.apache.org//mail2.html\">Mailing Lists</a> - Apache JMeter mailing lists.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T16:29:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aliesbelik/awesome-jmeter","categoryHTML":"<h2>Distributions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jmeter.apache.org/download_jmeter.cgi\">Download Apache JMeter</a> - Apache JMeter: Official downloads.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-14T16:29:07.000Z"},{"awesomeLis